Description: scOMM (single-cell Omics Multimodal Mapping) is an interpretable machine learning framework for supervised cell-type annotation and systematic benchmarking of multimodal single-cell data. It maps high-dimensional single-cell datasets to external reference atlases across RNA, chromatin accessibility, and multiomic assays, enabling consistent label transfer, cross-modality evaluation, and feature-importance analysis. scOMM is designed to support controlled comparisons of distinct single-cell technologies and integration strategies, facilitating the assessment of cell-type and cell-state resolution across modalities.
